Bring a large #pot of water to a boil with a @salt{pinch}. Halve, peel, and finely chop the @red onion{1}. Mince or grate the @garlic{2%cloves}. Finely chop the @parsley{1%bunch} and @tarragon{1%sprig}. Halve the @lemon{1}. Add the @fettuccine{6%ounce} to the boiling water and cook for about ~{10%minutes}, until al dente. Be sure to reserve ½ cup pasta water.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a large #pan over medium heat. Add the onion and season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until softened. Add the garlic and @mixed wild mushrooms{4%ounce} and season with salt and pepper. Cook for about ~{5%minutes}, until mushrooms are golden brown.

Add the tarragon, @veggie stock concentrate{1}, and ½ cup pasta water to the pan with the mushrooms. Cook for about ~{3%minutes}, until slightly reduced.

Add the @sour cream{2%tablespoon} and stir to combine, and cook for ~{3%minutes}.

Drain the pasta and add it to the pan with the sauce. Add a squeeze of lemon juice and half the parsley. Toss to combine.

Serve the fettuccine with a sprinkle of @parmesan cheese{¼%cup} and remaining parsley on top.